      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validated QoI (hemolysis index) must be directly the same scalar quantity used in the regulatory submission; no surrogate or proxy QoI permitted at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH), which is the same quantity used in the regulatory submission. However, the model outputs volume-averaged NIH whereas the clinical threshold applies to plasma-free haemoglobin; a minor translation step introduces unquantified uncertainty. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
