      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal use-error analysis must document all analyst-controlled inputs and demonstrate that plausible mis-specification does not change the accept/reject outcome for hemolysis.",
      "rationale": "No formal use-error analysis has been conducted. Sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to analyst choices (turbulence model constants, near-wall treatment, time-step) has not been systematically explored. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
