      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis power-law model form must be justified by mechanistic evidence; alternative model forms must be evaluated and the selected form must be shown to be appropriate for the shear-stress and exposure-time regime of the VAD.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law is used without systematic comparison to alternative hemolysis models (e.g., Arora, Taskin). Model form uncertainty is unquantified and represents a dominant epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
